"Indian (northern states): from Sanskrit <i>deva</i> ‘deity, lord’. This was a title used by ruling families in northern India. There is a Jat tribe called Deo. In northeastern India this name is spelled and pronounced   Deb  . Elsewhere, a common variant is   Dev  .","Italian: from a short form of the personal names <i>Amadeo</i>, <i>Laudadeo</i>, or <i>Sperindeo</i>, of which only the first now remains in use as a personal name."],"variants":[{"name":"Deb","meanings":["Indian (northeastern states): variant of   Deo  , found among Kayasthas."]},{"name":"Dev","meanings":["Indian: variant of   Deo  . In Maharashtra, Konkanastha Brahmins have a clan called Dev."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":63,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705188,"age":72,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705189,"age":107,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"D'Eu was born in 1152, in Essex, England. She had at least 2 sons with William De La Rokele I."},"et":{"1152–":"